  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) <strong>half </strong>your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>remaining garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-37-1705055040340-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-37-1705055040340-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-37-1705055040340-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-37-1705055040340-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-37-1705055040340-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle, then heat a pot with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add <strong>sliced garlic</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>sliced shallot</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped ginger</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pot with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant and crisp</p><p>Once crispy, carefully pour the oil into a heatproof bowl and set aside, reserving the pot – this is your <strong>crispy chilli oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-41-1705055044505-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-41-1705055044505-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-41-1705055044505-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-41-1705055044505-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-41-1705055044505-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate, large pot with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>remaining sliced shallot</strong>, <strong>remaining chopped ginger </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Combine your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>soy sauce</strong> with 1.2L <span class=\"text-purple\">[1.9L]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[2.5L]<strong> </span>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>soy stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-43-1705055049141-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-43-1705055049141-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-43-1705055049141-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-43-1705055049141-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-43-1705055049141-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>sushi rice </strong>and <strong>star anise </strong>and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the grains in the oil</p><p>Add the <strong>soy stock </strong>and cook for 25-30 min, stirring occasionally, or until the stock has thickened and the rice is cooked – this is your <strong>Japanese-style congee</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-42-1705055055269-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-42-1705055055269-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-42-1705055055269-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-42-1705055055269-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-42-1705055055269-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, reboil a full kettle</p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Wash, then chop the root from your <strong>pak choi</strong> and separate the leaves, discarding the root</p><p>Slice your<strong> chestnut mushrooms</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-40-1705055060194-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-40-1705055060194-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-40-1705055060194-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-40-1705055060194-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-40-1705055060194-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>pak choi leaves </strong>and <strong>sliced mushrooms</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil </strong>(or two!) with a generous splash of <strong>cold water</strong> and your <strong>sesame oil</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> then scrunch the foil around the vegetables to form a tightly sealed parcel[s] and add to a baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until the vegetables are tender – this is your <strong>sesame veg</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-38-1705055064896-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-38-1705055064896-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-38-1705055064896-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-38-1705055064896-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-38-1705055064896-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>egg[s]</strong> to the reserved pot, cover with <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for exactly 6 min, then fill a bowl of<strong> very cold water </strong>and add the <strong>cooked egg[s]</strong> to the bowl to cool down quickly</p><p>Peel the <strong>cooled egg[s]</strong> and slice in half</p><p>Season the <strong>halved egg[s] </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-30-1705055069137-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-30-1705055069137-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-30-1705055069137-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-30-1705055069137-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-30-1705055069137-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve your <strong>Japanese-style congee</strong> in a bowl (discard the star anise!) and top with the <strong>sesame veg</strong>, <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>and <strong>halved egg</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>crispy chilli oil</strong> and sprinkle with your <strong>crispy onions</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
